AUSTRALIAN
On flights between Jingapore and Melbourne we are pleased to
offer these outstanding wines from Australia.
PREECE
CHARDONNAY. 1997
The complex and elegant Preece Chardonnay is made from grapes grown
in the premium wine-making region of Victoria.
The 19Y/ vintage offers sweet fruit flavours, augmented by spicy
overtones and well-balanced acidity. A delightful wine to drink at any
time, with seafood or spicy dishes.
MITCHELTON
GOULBURN VALLEY SHIRAZ 1996
MITCHELTON
Australia's Goulburn Valley has been producing Shiraz of remarkable
depth and flavour for more than 130 years, a tradition that continues
with Mitchelton Goulburn Valley Shiraz.
The hallmarks of this wine are intense fruit flavours and a rounded,
mouth-filling texture. The wine is matured in oak barrels for 16 month:
and blended with small amounts of Grenache and Mourvedre to add
further earthiness and spice. The 1990 vintage offers a warm, mulberry
fruit aroma with a velvety, well-balanced palate - the perfect
accompaniment to beef or lamb dishes
PORT
THE CHAIRMAN'S LATE BOTTLED PORT
Like "Vintage Port", this is the wine of a single year but bottled
after o years in cask rather than 2 years and it is, therefore, ready
for drinking shortly after bottling.
The wine is from a single vineyard, the Qunita's Santa Madalena,
which lies on the eastern slopes of the Kio Torta. This is the best part
of the Douro Valley, the only place Fort wine can be produced.
This wine from the 1989 vintage has a delightful palate full of
richly concentrated fruit. It has a wonderful depth of flavour and in
the style of very fine Port, is long, well balanced and delicious to
drink.
The Chairman's
LATE BOILED
PORT
